                <note rend="inline" type="source">760g.61/62: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The High Commissioner at Constantinople</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bristol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Constantinople</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-04-08T17:00:00+03:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 8, 1921—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received 9:04 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>129. A Moscow radio dated April 6th announces the occupation of Erivan by the
                    Soviet forces. This apparently means the overthrow of the Vratzian
                    anti-Bolshevik Government in Armenia which had regained Erivan at the time of
                    the Bolshevik attack on Georgia. See my 64, February 24 [<hi rend="italic"
                        >21</hi>].<note n="48" xml:id="d887fn48">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bristol</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
